miscConds.notes:
During the pendency of this deferral, the Defendant agrees to:
-Commit no acts which rise to the level of probable cause in violation of the criminal laws of the state of Wisconsin, or of any other state, or of the United States of America.
-Comply with all conditions of bail or bond in this case.
-Pay a fine of $50 plus the costs of this action
-Comply with all conditions of probation for count 3. Violation of any rule of probation, or revocation from probation, constitutes a violation of this condition. Probation will be for a period of 2 years
-The defendant has obtained an evaluation and has begun the treatment regimen established for her. She will remain in compliance with those recommendations to include absolute sobriety. from alcohol and illegal drugs. 
-The parties agree, and the defendant understands, that the conditions of any bail or bond in effect on the plea date shall continue for the entire length of this agreement, and that any violation of the defendant's bond may result in bail jumping charges pursuant to Wis. Stat. 946.49. The defendant further understands that a charged violation of the bail or bond for which probable cause is found shall be a basis for the State to vacate this agreement.
-Defendant will keep Douglas County Clerk of Courts informed of his address and telephone number at all times, and stipulates that the sending of notice by regular mail to the address on file with the Clerk of Courts constitutes sufficient notice of any court hearings scheduled in this matter.  The non-appearance of the defendant may result in the issuance of an arrest warrant.

-If, at any time during the deferral period, the defendant has no complied with the conditions of this agreement, the State may at its discretion and upon notice the defendant, revoke the agreement and move the Court to enter judgment of conviction and the parties shall proceed to sentencing. At sentencing, the State shall be free to argue for any disposition it deems appropriate, up to and including the maximum sentence provided by law. 
-Except as otherwise provided in this agreement, the State must prove non-compliance with thus agreement by the preponderance of the evidence at a hearing subject to Wis. Stat. 911.01(4)(c).
-At the end of this deferral period or upon completion of all terms of this agreement, whichever is later, if the defendant has complied with the conditions of this agreement and provided proof of compliance when required, the State will move to dismiss this count with prejudice.
Pay as required by Clerk of Courts.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Alyssa Mary Gates

records.addlTxt:
11:11 AM Defendant Alyssa Mary Gates in court.  Attorney Joseph Foster Rosenthal in court for Alyssa Mary Gates.  Attorney Peter Marvin Kruger in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case. Defendant will plead to Counts 1 and 3, remaining charge dismissed. Placed on DJOC on Count 1, Count 3, 60 days jail I&S 2 years, conditions of probation to be $50 fine plus costs, DOC programming, maintain absolute sobriety and follow treatment program. Attorney Rosenthal agrees. No objection to bond conditions remaining in place.
Court recounts charges and possible penalties. Defendant pleads no contest to Counts 1 and 3. Court informs defendant of rights given up by their plea. Attorney stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. Court finds Defendant understands all the rights they are waiving by their plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered on Count 3 and deferred on Count 1 pursuant to DJOC. DA to monitor DJOC. All other charges dismissed.
Attorney Rosenthal makes statements. Asks court to accept recommendation.
Defendant makes statements.
Court orders on Count 3 60 days jail imposed and stayed 2 years, conditions of maintain absolute sobriety, $50 fine plus costs, DOC programming.

1:27 PM Prosecuting attorney Peter James Marvin Kruger in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Alyssa Mary Gates appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman appeared by video for Alyssa Mary Gates. Defendant does not have an alternate address to provide the court. Attorney/Defendant acknowledges receipt of the complaint, waives a formal reading, enters pleas of not guilty to the misdemeanor count(s), and requests a preliminary hearing. State asks for $1,000 cash bail. No contact with Victim 1, Victim 2, any other children in the home, and no return to the address on the complaint. Indicates that that the victims are asking for the no contact for themselves and on behalf of the other children in the home. Recites reasons victims are asking for the no contact condition. No local criminal history, but cites danger of the allegations and concerns over ability to follow court orders. Court asks for initials of other children in the home. Attorney Hoffman indicates that she has lived in Douglas county for the last 3 years, has local employment, and children in the area. No history of FTAs and does not have a significant criminal history. Asks for high dollar signature bond. State provides initials of children in the home (MOS, JCN, and MGN). Court quashes arrest warrant quashed. 
Court orders $5,000 signature bond with conditions of no contact with Victim 1, Victim 2, MOS, JCN, MGN, and no return to the address on the complaint.
